title: Bug 124761: Unable to extract data when adding two filters
description: When adding two filters ('State is equal to CA' and 'EmployeeId is Top 10') to the report, the data cannot be extracted.
OB:
Description: When adding two filters ('State is equal to CA' and 'EmployeeId is Top 10') to the report, the data cannot be extracted.
Steps to reproduce:
1. Import the attached report.
2. Preview the report.
EB:
Actual result: The data cannot be extracted.
Expected result: The intersection set of the data 'State is equal to CA' and the data 'EmployeeId is Top 10' should be displayed.
SR: The issue needs to be investigated and fixed to ensure that the data can be extracted correctly when both filters are applied.
